  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ED - Leading through Learning Global Platform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(USAID Bureau for Democracy, Development, and Innovation (DDI)):  The Leading through Learning Global Platform (LTLGP) activity will support, expand, and leverage a global platform of learning networks as a means of applying the best available evidence across the full breadth of USAID education investments. With a particular focus on developing evidence-based technical tools, improving knowledge and skills in USAID education sector priority areas and the COVID-19 response in education, and promoting increased collaboration on best practices, this activity will systematically increase the use of evidence-based practices in the design, implementation, and evaluation of USAID&apos;s education programs. Building on and complementing previous USAID education efforts to strengthen capacity in the sector, including the Data and Evidence for Education Programs (DEEP) and YouthPower2 activities, the LTLGP activity will continue to support knowledge sharing and tool development iteratively as USAID&apos;s education programs evolve. In addition, the LTLGP activity will strengthen capacity in the education sector and improve collaboration through sector-specific learning networks that are inclusive of marginalized populations, higher education, new and underutilized partners,  and public and private actors. Technical guidance/tools, capacity strengthening, and  skill-building activities for evidence-based practice will be expanded to improve the COVID-19 response in education and respond to the wide-ranging impacts of COVID-19 on education systems. Overall, because evidence-informed education programming will lead to more effective programs, the LTLGP activity will ultimately result in sustained, measurable improvements in learning outcomes and skill development for beneficiaries of USAID&apos;s education investments.</narrative>
  </description>
